      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: report download path in browser click action result",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen the browser tool's click action triggers a file download, the agent currently has no way to know the download completed. This PR adds download detection to click actions so the result includes `download.path` when a download occurs.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **pw-session.ts**: Track `lastDownloadPath` in `PageState` after the page-level download listener auto-saves a file\n- **pw-tools-core.interactions.ts**: `clickViaPlaywright()` now clears `lastDownloadPath` before clicking and polls briefly (1.5s) after click for download completion. Returns `{ downloadPath }` when a download was captured\n- **browser-tool.ts**: Updated tool description to mention download detection on click actions\n\n## How it works\n\n1. Before clicking, `lastDownloadPath` is cleared\n2. The click executes normally\n3. After the click, a short poll checks if the page-level download listener saved a new file\n4. If yes, the download path is included in the click result, so the agent knows the download succeeded\n\nFixes #93250",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93250-Bug-No-notification-when-br",
